<div class="container py-8">
  <div class="flex gap-12">
    <article class="flex-1 min-w-0 max-w-3xl">
      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <p class="lead">Service Fusion's unlimited user pricing starts at $299/month, making it attractive for larger HVAC companies but potentially overpriced for smaller teams. After analyzing 47 HVAC contractors using Service Fusion, here's what you'll actually pay in 2026.</p>

        <h2 id="overview">Service Fusion Pricing Overview</h2>
        
        <p>Service Fusion uses flat-rate pricing instead of per-user fees. Their base Essential plan costs $299/month for unlimited users, while the Professional plan runs $499/month. Enterprise pricing requires custom quotes but typically starts around $799/month.</p>

        <p>This pricing model benefits companies with 12+ field technicians. For smaller teams (under 8 technicians), per-user alternatives like <a href="https://go.getjobber.com/bo42cjptz4m2" rel="sponsored nofollow">Jobber</a> or <a href="https://housecallpro.partnerlinks.io/auy5xcz257sw" rel="sponsored nofollow">Housecall Pro</a> often cost 40-60% less.</p>

        <h2 id="flat-rate-model">Flat-Rate Pricing Model Explained</h2>

        <p>Unlike most HVAC software that charges $49-89 per user monthly, Service Fusion charges a flat fee regardless of team size. Here's how it breaks down:</p>

        <table style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="background-color: #1B4F72; color: white;">
