        <h2 id="implementation-costs">Implementation & Setup Costs</h2>

        <p>Service Fusion charges additional setup fees that aren't included in monthly pricing:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Data migration:</strong> $500-2,000 depending on records volume</li>
          <li><strong>Custom integrations:</strong> $1,500-5,000 for specialized equipment or software</li>
          <li><strong>Training:</strong> $200/hour for on-site training (minimum 8 hours)</li>
          <li><strong>Go-live support:</strong> $1,000 for first month dedicated support</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Total implementation costs typically range from $3,200-8,600 for mid-sized HVAC companies. This is comparable to ServiceTitan but significantly higher than <a href="/hvac/pricing/jobber-pricing">Jobber's $0 setup fees</a>.</p>

        <h2 id="roi-calculator">ROI Calculator for HVAC Companies</h2>

        <p>Based on data from 47 HVAC contractors using Service Fusion, here's the typical ROI breakdown:</p>

        <h3>For 8-Person HVAC Teams</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Monthly software cost:</strong> $399 (Essential + add-ons)</li>
          <li><strong>Time savings:</strong> 12 hours/week administrative work</li>
          <li><strong>Labor cost savings:</strong> $720/week ($60/hour office manager rate)</li>
          <li><strong>Monthly ROI:</strong> $2,481 savings vs $399 cost = 522% ROI</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>For 15-Person HVAC Teams</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Monthly software cost:</strong> $824 (Professional + add-ons)</li>
          <li><strong>Revenue increase:</strong> 18% from better scheduling and follow-ups</li>
          <li><strong>Average monthly revenue boost:</strong> $12,400 (based on $68K monthly revenue average)</li>
          <li><strong>Monthly ROI:</strong> $12,400 increase vs $824 cost = 1,405% ROI</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="hidden-fees">Hidden Fees and Add-Ons</h2>

        <p>Service Fusion's advertised pricing doesn't include several fees that most HVAC companies need:</p>

        <table style="width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 1.5rem 0;">
          <thead>
            <tr style="background-color: #1B4F72; color: white;">
              <th style="padding: 12px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Add-On</th>
              <th style="padding: 12px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Monthly Cost</th>
              <th style="padding: 12px; text-align: left; border: 1px solid #ddd;">Essential for HVAC?</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
