            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>Most HVAC companies end up paying $110-185/month in add-ons on top of base pricing. Factor this into your total cost calculations.</p>

        <h2 id="when-to-choose">When Service Fusion Makes Sense</h2>

        <p>Service Fusion is cost-effective for HVAC companies that meet these criteria:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>12+ field technicians:</strong> Flat-rate pricing becomes advantageous</li>
          <li><strong>High job volume:</strong> 200+ jobs per month to justify setup costs</li>
          <li><strong>Complex operations:</strong> Multiple locations, extensive inventory tracking</li>
          <li><strong>Growth planning:</strong> Expecting to double team size within 2 years</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Companies with fewer than 10 technicians typically save money with per-user alternatives. Our <a href="/hvac/guides/how-to-choose-hvac-software">HVAC software selection guide</a> includes a decision framework based on team size.</p>

        <h2 id="alternatives">Better Alternatives for Most HVAC Companies</h2>

        <p>Based on pricing analysis, here are better options for different company sizes:</p>

        <h3>For 2-8 Person Teams</h3>
        <p><a href="https://go.getjobber.com/vcuhehgs796s" rel="sponsored nofollow">Jobber</a> typically costs 35-50% less than Service Fusion for smaller teams. It includes scheduling, invoicing, payments, and customer management for $49/user/month. Read our <a href="/hvac/crm/jobber-vs-servicetitan">Jobber vs ServiceTitan comparison</a> for detailed analysis.</p>

        <h3>For 5-12 Person Teams</h3>
        <p><a href="https://housecallpro.partnerlinks.io/auy5xcz257sw" rel="sponsored nofollow">Housecall Pro</a> offers more advanced features than Jobber at $61/user/month. Better for companies needing robust reporting and customer communication tools. See our <a href="/hvac/pricing/housecall-pro-pricing">Housecall Pro pricing breakdown</a>.</p>

        <h3>For 15+ Person Teams</h3>
        <p>Service Fusion becomes competitive at this size, but consider ServiceTitan if you need advanced features like dynamic pricing, performance management, and enterprise reporting. Our <a href="/hvac/crm/servicetitan-vs-housecall-pro">ServiceTitan comparison</a> covers the differences.</p>

        <h2>Tools That Pair Well With Service Fusion</h2>

        <p>HVAC companies using Service Fusion often add these tools for complete business management:</p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Time Tracking:</strong> <a href="https://get.toggl.com/f71dwhbrzvzz" rel="sponsored nofollow">Toggl Track</a> for accurate job costing and payroll ($9/user/month)</li>
          <li><strong>Lead Generation:</strong> <a href="https://get.apollo.io/fxnpnadnv4lb" rel="sponsored nofollow">Apollo.io</a> for prospecting commercial accounts ($49/user/month)</li>
          <li><strong>Call Tracking:</strong> <a href="https://partners.callrail.com/ut5waejxy35l" rel="sponsored nofollow">CallRail</a> for marketing ROI tracking ($45/month)</li>
        </ul>

        <p>These integrations add $103-153/month but provide comprehensive business intelligence that Service Fusion lacks natively.</p>

        <p>Service Fusion's unlimited user pricing works well for larger HVAC companies but often costs more than per-user alternatives for smaller teams. Calculate your total costs including add-ons and setup fees before committing to a 12-month contract.</p>
